Puntpdate, week 12!

Φtop of the list starting to take shape - could be quite the race for P1
ΦMorstead is back baybee (he'll keep showing up with a Jets logo for a bit bc that's where the majority of his punts have been)

#nflverse https://t.co/v332dbZPmb

12 weeks into the season, I have computed pythagorean expectations based on @fboutsiders adjusted pythagorean theorem and compared them to the actual wins of each team. The table is sorted by expected wins based on points scored and points allowed.
Data: #nflverse https://t.co/ePlTmPDrgP

This updated version adds transparency to the field and to non-scoring drives. Only scoring drives end in a white point. Also added time of possession and number of plays. Still work in progress. 
#nflverse https://t.co/8L4rVSv42U

Summary of NFL Week 12 price changes:

Many bettors are eager to call a top on the Patriots after the spread v the Titans widened 4 points the last week. Maybe sentiment is a bit overheated, but that 4 point move isn't all Patriots-related  #nflverse

data: @4for4football https://t.co/0fkK7CAlED

No mercy for Rams bettors in 2021

#nflverse https://t.co/oxc01Sn01Z https://t.co/LBKsWsczSV

Is there any explanation for why MIN is so so bad when leading? It comes back to bite them every week and (aside from noise of a small sample?) I don't see an easy explanation for why this is the case. Any ideas?
#nflverse https://t.co/CFb7SXYDS3

if we evaluate user performance in lee sharpe's nfl prediction game the way we would for a traditional portfolio manager, we can more easily detect who is likely skilled and who is likely benefiting from outsized luck. 

#nflverse https://t.co/JssVqIJDQU

the circa survivor bloodbath in color 

favorites' unprecedented early season success lulled entrants into a false sense of security before the underdog revenge tour caught fire the last three weeks 

< 1% of entrants remain #nflverse #rstats #CircaSportsMillion https://t.co/sHsCnZpDxw https://t.co/wgBUVLiNge

Saquon Barkley is the Jameis Winston of Running Backs.

Since entering the league, he ranks 3rd in percentage of runs over 20 yards, but 2nd in percentage of runs below 0 yards.

Like @Danny_Heifetz says, on every play, Saquon either hits a home run or strikes out.

#nflverse https://t.co/W5YgTxmCch

A preview infographic for the huge Pats-Bills showdown this week:
 #BillsMafia have been better on offense and defense, but Pats are on a hot streak
 Mac-Allen QB Battle will define the game
 AFC East lead at stake

Data: #nflverse | Inspiration: @bestballstats https://t.co/AOKMxSeL9c

Some RB clustering going into week 12 to check out while watching "The Game:"
Cluster Labels:
1) The replaceable's
2) The bellcow backs
3) The league's best rushers
4) The pass-catching/committee backs
5) The generally inefficient backs
